description: The Myanmar opposition leader, Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, said on Thursday that she would be “above the president” if her party wins in general elections on Sunday, defying a constitutional ban.
title: Aung San Suu Kyi Discusses Coming Vote
title_page: Aung San Suu Kyi Discusses Coming Vote - Video - NYTimes.com
text: The Myanmar opposition leader, Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, said on Thursday that she would be “above the president” if her party wins in general elections on Sunday, defying a constitutional ban.
